WEBVTT

00:05.272 --> 00:06.240 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.273 --> 00:07.241 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.274 --> 00:09.009 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:09.042 --> 00:12.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight:
It's the eve of the final
presidential debate.

00:12.246 --> 00:17.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton prepares behind
closed doors,
while we consider Donald Trump's
claims of

00:18.018 --> 00:19.887 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a media conspiracy.

00:19.920 --> 00:24.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Also ahead
this Tuesday,
John Yang reports from Nevada,
where a Republican

00:24.057 --> 00:28.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
split on Donald Trump creates a
close race
for a crucial Senate seat.

00:28.428 --> 00:34.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, as the
international community
struggles with a refugee crisis,
how Uganda

00:34.067 --> 00:38.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is becoming one of the most
welcoming countries
for those fleeing conflict.

00:38.071 --> 00:42.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Camps tend
to confine
people, whereas, in Uganda, when
refugees

00:42.576 --> 00:48.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
arrive, they are issued legal
I.D.s that entitle
them to move freely anywhere in
the country

00:48.181 --> 00:51.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to find a job, start a business,
put their
children in school.

00:51.985 --> 00:54.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All that and
more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:54.421 --> 00:58.725 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:58.759 --> 01:11.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's three weeks
to go until
Election Day, just 24 hours
until the last

01:11.772 --> 01:17.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
presidential debate, and charges
of vote fraud
and media bias are swirling.

01:17.477 --> 01:22.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, the current occupant of
the White House
dismissed such talk, and rebuked
the candidate

01:22.816 --> 01:27.821 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
behind it.

01:27.854 --> 01:33.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was a Rose Garden welcome for
the Italian
prime minister, and President
Obama used it

01:33.427 --> 01:36.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to call out Donald Trump on his
claims of
a rigged election.

01:37.030 --> 01:39.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
You start whining before the
game is even

01:39.333 --> 01:43.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
over, if whenever things are
going badly for
you or you lose, you start
blaming somebody

01:43.470 --> 01:47.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
else, then you don't have what
it takes to
be in this job.

01:47.674 --> 01:51.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trump shot back
this afternoon
in Colorado Springs.

01:51.044 --> 01:54.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
But they even want to try and
rig the election

01:55.015 --> 01:59.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at the polling booths, where so
many cities
are corrupt, and you see that.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.688 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And voter fraud is all too
common.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then they criticize us for
saying that.

02:03.757 --> 02:07.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Running mate Mike
Pence joined
in.

02:07.094 --> 02:12.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Visiting Republican Party
offices in rural
North Carolina that were
firebombed over the

02:12.866 --> 02:19.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weekend, he insisted voter fraud
is a reality,
and called for voters to be on
the lookout.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.907 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

02:20.941 --> 02:22.743 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE PENCE (R-IN), Vice
Presidential Candidate:
Donald Trump and I are
encouraging all of

02:22.776 --> 02:27.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our supporters around the
country and frankly
American, whatever their
politics, to take

02:27.681 --> 02:34.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the opportunity to be involved
in a respectful
way in providing accountability
at our polling

02:34.087 --> 02:35.922 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
places.

02:35.956 --> 02:40.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Pence also
complained of media
bias and what he called scant
coverage of

02:40.227 --> 02:42.029 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
negative news about Clinton.

02:42.062 --> 02:48.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The latest such news involved
communications
between the FBI and a senior
State Department

02:48.335 --> 02:52.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
official who wanted one of
Clinton's e-mails
reclassified.

02:52.739 --> 02:54.641 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It wasn't.

02:54.674 --> 03:00.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But last night in Green Bay,
Wisconsin, Trump
charged there's collusion in the
Obama administration

03:00.414 --> 03:02.382 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to help Clinton.

03:02.416 --> 03:08.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The candidate's wife, Melania,
was on CNN,
claiming that the sexual assault
allegations

03:08.388 --> 03:10.323 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
against her husband are not
true.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MELANIA TRUMP, Wife of Donald
Trump: I believe
my husband.

03:11.658 --> 03:13.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I believe my husband.

03:13.126 --> 03:15.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This was all organized from the
opposition.

03:15.429 --> 03:21.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Former "People"
magazine writer
Natasha Stoynoff is one of the
accusers.

03:21.334 --> 03:24.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She stated that Trump forced
himself on her
in 2005.

03:24.905 --> 03:31.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, today, the publication
reported that
six of her colleagues and close
friends corroborate

03:31.278 --> 03:33.080 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
her account.

03:33.113 --> 03:39.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Clinton remained out
of the public
eye today, even as poll after
poll offered

03:39.052 --> 03:40.854 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
her good news.

03:40.887 --> 03:46.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Washington Post reported she
has a clear
advantage in the latest survey
of battleground

03:46.093 --> 03:47.894 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
states.

03:47.928 --> 03:54.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And a USA Today poll found 68
percent of young
voters favor the Democratic
nominee, to 20

03:54.201 --> 03:55.969 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
percent for Trump.

03:56.002 --> 04:01.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All of this sets the stage for
tomorrow night's
third and final encounter
between the two

04:01.274 --> 04:03.677 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
nominees, this one in Las Vegas.

04:03.710 --> 04:08.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In the day's
other news:
Iraqi forces slowed their
advance on Mosul

04:08.181 --> 04:12.819 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in its second day, as they
reached larger
towns on the outskirts.

04:12.853 --> 04:16.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Humanitarian groups warned the
city's one
million people could face a
disaster.

04:16.790 --> 04:19.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But President Obama said plans
are in place
to avert a crisis.

04:19.860 --> 04:22.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will explore the situation in
Mosul later
in the program.

04:22.596 --> 04:28.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next door in
Syria, Russian
halted strikes on Aleppo today,
ahead of their

04:28.335 --> 04:32.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
call for a short-term stop to
all fighting
on Thursday.

04:32.739 --> 04:36.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's meant to allow humanitarian
aid into
that ravaged city.

04:36.476 --> 04:41.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in Moscow, the Russian
defense minister
warned militant groups to
evacuate when the

04:41.748 --> 04:43.617 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
fighting stops.

04:43.650 --> 04:46.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SERGEI SHOIGU, Russian Defense
Minister (through
translator): We call on the
leadership of

04:46.086 --> 04:50.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
countries that have influence
over armed groups
in Eastern Aleppo to convince
their leaders

04:50.123 --> 04:52.926 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to stop military action and
abandon the city.

04:52.959 --> 04:57.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everyone truly interested in the
fastest possible
stabilization should take
genuine political

04:57.631 --> 05:00.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
steps and not continue shuffling
political
papers.

05:00.700 --> 05:04.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thursday's pause
in the fighting
is set to last eight hours.

05:04.471 --> 05:09.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A United Nations spokesman
complained today
that that's not nearly enough
time to get

05:09.809 --> 05:12.679 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
humanitarian convoys in and out
of Aleppo.

05:12.712 --> 05:16.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: A temporary
halt to the
fighting in Yemen is also in the
works.

05:16.583 --> 05:21.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The country's warring factions
agreed today
to a 72-hour cease-fire,
beginning shortly

05:21.188 --> 05:23.023 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
before midnight Wednesday.

05:23.056 --> 05:25.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's to allow much-needed
humanitarian aid
to be delivered.

05:25.659 --> 05:30.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In Iran, a court
has sentenced
an Iranian-American businessman
and his father

05:30.730 --> 05:33.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to 10 years in prison each.

05:33.500 --> 05:36.570 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Siamak Namazi was detained a
year ago.

05:36.603 --> 05:40.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
His 80-year-old father was
arrested in February.

05:40.073 --> 05:44.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today's announcement says they
were sentenced
for -- quote -- "cooperating
with the hostile

05:44.077 --> 05:45.979 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
government of America."

05:46.012 --> 05:48.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Back in this
country, for
a fifth straight year, Social
Security recipients

05:49.015 --> 05:52.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and federal retirees will get
just a tiny
bump in benefits.

05:52.953 --> 05:57.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The annual cost-of-living hike
announced today
is three-tenths of a percent.

05:57.390 --> 06:01.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The average monthly Social
Security payment
is $1,238.

06:01.628 --> 06:06.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That means the increase for the
coming year
will be less than $4 a month.

06:06.466 --> 06:11.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Wall Street moved
higher today,
thanks to some strong earnings.

06:11.238 --> 06:15.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 75
points to close near 18162.

06:15.508 --> 06:21.248 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 44 points, and
the S&amp;P 500
added 13.

06:21.281 --> 06:25.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And the
original ruby slippers
from "The Wizard of Oz" will get
a makeover

06:25.552 --> 06:28.355 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
if the Smithsonian can raise
$300,000.

06:28.388 --> 06:32.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's asking the public to help
on the crowdfunding
Web site Kickstarter.

06:32.559 --> 06:37.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The ruby slippers are nearly 80
years old,
and showing their age, at the
National Museum

06:37.297 --> 06:39.165 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of Natural History in
Washington.

06:39.199 --> 06:44.037 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The institution wants to repair
them and build
a new display.

06:44.070 --> 06:48.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what's driving
the idea that the media is
rigging the election;

06:48.575 --> 06:53.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a tight race in Nevada as
Democrats try to
take back the Senate; the
looming humanitarian

06:53.913 --> 07:08.762 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crisis in Iraq; and much more.

07:08.795 --> 07:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Claims of news media bias in
politics are
certainly nothing new.

07:13.199 --> 07:18.171 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what of Donald Trump's
accusation that
the press is actually
responsible for rigging

07:18.204 --> 07:21.241 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the presidential election
against him?

07:21.274 --> 07:25.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To explore that notion, we are
joined by Jim
Rutenberg, media columnist for
The New York

07:25.545 --> 07:27.981 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Times, and Robert Lichter.

07:28.014 --> 07:33.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's director of the center for
Media and
Public Affairs at George Mason
University.

07:33.353 --> 07:35.388 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we welcome both of you to
the program.

07:35.422 --> 07:37.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm going to start with you,
Robert Lichter.

07:37.757 --> 07:41.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump is saying that the
media -- and
I'm quoting -- is being -- that
the election

07:41.895 --> 07:48.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is being rigged by what he calls
the dishonest,
distorted media pushing Hillary
Clinton.

07:48.034 --> 07:51.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have studied the American
media for, what,
decades?

07:51.871 --> 07:54.808 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is there a grain of truth to
what he says?

07:54.841 --> 07:57.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT LICHTER, George Mason
University: Well,
when people say the media are
biased, they

07:57.644 --> 08:02.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
usually mean somebody is getting
too much
attention, more than he
deserves, and his

08:02.415 --> 08:04.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
coverage is more favorable than
he should
get.

08:04.751 --> 08:06.619 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Donald Trump is a news magnet.

08:06.653 --> 08:10.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He gets more attention than
anybody else,
but a lot of that attention
compares him either

08:10.924 --> 08:12.659 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with Hitler or Mussolini.

08:12.692 --> 08:17.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So studies show what our eyes
see, that Trump
gets a lot of coverage, that his
coverage

08:17.897 --> 08:19.699 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is very negative.

08:19.733 --> 08:23.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has managed the considerable
feat of getting
more negative coverage than
Hillary Clinton,

08:23.169 --> 08:25.939 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
who has issues in her own right.

08:25.972 --> 08:28.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that -- so you could
make a case that
there is bias.

08:28.708 --> 08:36.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think the question is whether
the traditional
definitions of bias apply to
such a nontraditional

08:36.349 --> 08:37.884 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
candidate as Donald Trump.

08:37.917 --> 08:39.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Jim Rutenberg,
how do you see
this?

08:39.786 --> 08:42.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You write about this stuff
frequently for
The Times.

08:42.255 --> 08:46.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM RUTENBERG, The New York
Times: I think
I would agree with that
assessment to a degree.

08:46.326 --> 08:50.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One thing is, though, that
Donald Trump's
candidacy has been so amazing
and has been

08:50.563 --> 08:54.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
such -- it has had such a
can't-look-away
quality, because he says things
that we're

08:54.167 --> 08:57.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not used to hearing from the
standard-bearer
oft Republican Party.

08:57.470 --> 09:03.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, to the extent that some of
the things
are about the appearances of
women, what have

09:03.243 --> 09:08.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you, what we just heard on the
"Access Hollywood"
leaked tape of him discussing
his behavior

09:08.181 --> 09:13.486 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
with women, was at best
descriptions of groping,
there's going to be a reaction
to it.

09:13.520 --> 09:16.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The press is going to cover
that, and it's
going to, yes, be negative, but
it is also

09:16.656 --> 09:18.324 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
what it is.

09:18.358 --> 09:21.027 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's a pretty accurate
description of what
he said in that tape, for
instance.

09:21.060 --> 09:23.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let's take
this a little
bit further.

09:23.897 --> 09:28.701 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
What Donald Trump -- Bob
Lichter, what Donald
Trump is saying is that the
media is in collusion

09:28.735 --> 09:30.703 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with the Clinton campaign.

09:30.737 --> 09:34.474 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What evidence is there that that
could possibly
be true?

09:34.507 --> 09:38.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT LICHTER: Well, they have
been so nice
to her about her e-mails, I
think, is a piece

09:38.344 --> 09:40.146 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of evidence.

09:40.180 --> 09:43.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's perfectly obvious, and,
again, studies
show that her coverage is more
negative than

09:43.850 --> 09:44.784 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
positive.

09:44.818 --> 09:45.785 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
There's been...

09:45.819 --> 09:46.786 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

09:46.820 --> 09:48.655 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Wait a minute.

09:48.688 --> 09:53.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was one story about a
member of the
Clinton organization passing
along information

09:53.092 --> 09:54.127 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ahead of a debate.

09:54.160 --> 09:55.128 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is that right?

09:55.161 --> 09:56.129 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT LICHTER: Right.

