halting, shy English.

42:06.023 --> 42:07.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What would you like to do when
you grow up?

42:07.458 --> 42:09.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUDENT: When I grow up, I want
to be a doctor
and to help my mother.

42:09.961 --> 42:12.130 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: How about
you, David?

42:12.163 --> 42:13.865 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What would you like to do when
you grow up?

42:13.898 --> 42:15.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
STUDENT: I wish to be a pilot.

42:15.733 --> 42:18.169 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: You want to
be a pilot?

42:18.202 --> 42:19.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
STUDENT: Yes.

42:19.203 --> 42:20.171 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Yes.

42:20.204 --> 42:21.439 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Where would you like to go?

42:21.472 --> 42:23.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUDENT: Every place, America,
like, I guess,
everywhere.

42:23.674 --> 42:26.177 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: America and
everywhere.

42:26.210 --> 42:28.112 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
STUDENT: Yes.

42:28.146 --> 42:32.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Possible,
but like their
chance of a good education here,
with lottery-like

42:32.683 --> 42:33.785 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
odds.

42:33.818 --> 42:37.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
America admitted 70,000 refugees
last year.

42:37.321 --> 42:42.727 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
