students take
at least one civics class.

45:33.297 --> 45:36.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, how are teachers dealing
with this kind
of campaign?

45:36.567 --> 45:38.235 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We hear from Richard House.

45:38.269 --> 45:41.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He teaches seventh grade civics
at Gunston
Middle School in Arlington,
Virginia.

45:41.606 --> 45:44.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Chris Cavanaugh, who teaches
government
to juniors and seniors at
Plainfield High

45:44.809 --> 45:45.977 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
School in Indiana.

45:46.010 --> 45:47.745 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
