perhaps does not
encourage debate.

51:41.565 --> 51:44.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It doesn't push the debate or
conversation
forward.

51:44.335 --> 51:48.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, you want to avoid the
politics of
the personal attacks.

51:48.339 --> 51:53.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there have only been a
couple kids that
I have had to admonish for that.

51:53.344 --> 52:01.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we try to -- it's difficult,
because we're
trying to promote civic
discourse, civil discourse.

52:01.218 --> 52:05.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, unfortunately, we don't see
that in the
adult world as much as -- we
don't see it

52:05.689 --> 52:07.458 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
modeled for them as much as it
should be.

52:07.491 --> 52:11.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
Chris Cavanaugh
from Plainfield High in Indiana
and Richard

52:11.428 --> 52:13.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
House from Gunston Middle School
