continent.

52:32.316 --> 52:38.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Terror in Europe" looks at
government attempts
to counter extremism, revealing
missteps and

52:38.088 --> 52:44.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
systemic breakdowns in the
run-up to the Charlie
Hebdo, Paris and Brussels
attacks.

52:44.128 --> 52:49.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: As recruits returned
to Europe,
the authorities in France and
Belgium were

52:49.633 --> 52:51.101 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
overwhelmed.

52:51.135 --> 52:55.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Every
week, people
would come back from Syria.

52:55.839 --> 52:57.007 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There was nothing except Syria.

52:57.041 --> 52:58.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was all about Syria.

52:58.742 --> 53:02.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were so many cases related
to Syria
that people who should have been
watched just

53:02.312 --> 53:04.148 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
could not be.

53:04.181 --> 53:07.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Clearly, we can't do everything,
and we didn't
have the means -- we still don't
-- to monitor

53:07.785 --> 53:09.686 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
all of this.

53:09.720 --> 53:13.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LOUIS CAPRIOLI, Former French
Domestic Intelligence
Counterterror Chief (through
translator):

53:13.657 --> 53:17.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That brings up the issue of
having to make
choices.

53:17.461 --> 53:25.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That is, among all the
possibilities of targets
to monitor, thousands of targets
to monitor,

53:25.302 --> 53:28.439 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it's necessary to make choices.

53:28.472 --> 53:35.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NARRATOR: In June 2014, French
spy chiefs
made a fateful decision.

53:35.779 --> 53:41.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For the last three years, they
had been monitoring
al-Qaida veterans of the
Buttes-Chaumont gang,

53:41.118 --> 53:44.154 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Cherif Kouachi and his brother
Said.

53:44.188 --> 53:51.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meanwhile, Kouachi's old
associate Amedy Coulibaly
had just been released from
prison.

53:51.862 --> 53:57.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
French domestic intelligence now
decided to
stop watching them and shift
surveillance

53:57.568 --> 54:00.170 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
